name: Spacious 1 BR / 1 BA Living in Russian Hill
description:
A beautiful, spacious apartment in one of the most coveted, quaint, safe, walkable neighborhood. This large 1-Bedroom has a formal dining room, new bathroom with original clawfoot tub, living room and kitchen. The cable car is at your doorstep and famous Lombard street just 5 blocks away.

It is not directly located on the cable car line and very quiet. Several buses will take you downtown, to BART and caltrain station.

neighborhood_overview:
Russian Hill is a neighborhood with that rare advantage of being tucked away, yet central to almost everything. From this flat you can walk to Union Square, the Marina, Pacific Heights, Aquatic Park, Chinatown, or North Beach in about 15 minutes.

In May 2015, safety app "Go" found Russian Hill San Francisco's safest neighborhood for walking.

Walker's paradise: 96pts walk score and 94pts transit score. Source: https://www.walkscore.com/CA/San_Francisco/Russian_Hill

An upscale, safe and well-established San Francisco neighborhood, Russian Hill offers stunning views, vibrant businesses, and plenty of local history. Many of the city's top attractions and best restaurants can be found here.
